<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 1:52PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Lee and
southwestern Scott Counties through 230 PM EDT...
At 152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pennington Gap, or near Jonesville, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Jonesville, Pennington Gap, St. Charles, Jasper, Dryden and
Pattonsville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
